    <note>Shen(2) Jichang [1445] His great grandfather, Chengliang [3733] (father's funerary inscription has Chenghui], had the same generational name as Chengli [1442] and both families were from Huzhou, although Chengli was from Wucheng and Jichang was from Wukang. His ancestor, probably Tingpin [20882], moved to Hangzhou, Qiantang xian and lived there for two generations. Wang(2) Anli says he does not know the reason for the move. If, however, the two lineages were related [and probably also related to the lineage of Shen(2) Zhou [7323] et. al., then the reason is clear. Jichang's grandfather, Yu(2) [20883], died in Zhenzhou where he was prefect, and was buried there. From then on, the family address was Zhenzhou, Yangzi xian. Jichang was Bo's [7326] son, Shutong's [1458] brother, Wang(2) Yi(3)'s [7082] son-in-law, Wang(2) Anshi's [1762] brother-in-law, Zhang(2) Fu(3)'s [7012] father-in-law, and Zeng Gong's [7364] friend. He was dismissed from office in 1087 because he had been a supporter of Wang(2) Anshi. XCB, 403.1a; SHY:ZG, 66.37a; Wang Anli, WJ, 7.5b-10b. CBD, 1, 694.</note>
